 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Ethics, Compliance and Privacy Analyst BD 2,556 reviews Franklin Lakes, NJ BD 2,556 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job Company Job Description Summary 
The Ethics, Compliance and Privacy Analyst will support team members, including the Deputy Chief Compliance Officer, Enterprise Compliance & Operations, Ethics Office, Privacy, and Transparency functions. The Analyst is expected to demonstrate a comprehensive understanding of BD Values in his/her work while maintaining the highest level of personal and professional conduct. He/She should exhibit behaviors consistent with The BD WAY and approach opportunities with a growth mindset. The Analyst shall seek and seize opportunities to identify and prioritize needs based on risk level and strategic importance. 
 
This is a participative, hands-on role. The Analyst will work independently under strict deadlines, will manage competing priorities, and must handle multiple tasks efficiently. The ability to collaboratively interact with staff (at all levels of the organization) in a fast-paced environment, demonstrating a high level of confidentiality and discretion is crucial to this role. The ideal candidate will be exceedingly well organized, proactive, flexible, strategic and enjoy the challenges of working in a global group of diverse people and programs. 
Job Description 
Job Duties & Responsibilities 
Review and analyze external enforcement landscape and industry trade association codes; provide regular updates on these matters for E&C LT; analyze relevant cases and make recommendations for improvements to compliance program based on enforcement trends and learnings 
 Analyze internal compliance program data points to identify trends and make recommendations to optimize various program campaigns. Monitor year over year behavioral insights of training performance for future improvements to online training 
Regularly develop dashboards and presentations of key Ethics Office and other compliance related data for management 
Drafting, Editing & Finalizing Documents, including compliance policies and procedures 
Manage and lead Special Compliance Projects/ Assignments
 Meeting Facilitation (e.g., scheduling LT and other various team meetings, agenda preparation, meeting minutes, track and manage action items) 
Facilitate larger meetings within assigned groups – as appropriate, liaise with the relevant Core Admin to help with logistics (e.g., Global Town Halls, practice area team meetings, meetings with other third parties/vendors) 
Collaborate and communicate effectively with Core Admin staff and the Executive Assistant to the Chief Ethics & Compliance Officer to ensure milestones for key projects are met and meetings are effective with appropriate follow up 
Practice Area-Specific Job Duties and Expectations: 
Awareness and commitment to the Ethics & Compliance Mission and Key Driver Goals 
Develop dashboards, presentation and training materials for the CECO and other members of the E&C Department, the Compliance and Ethics Committee, the Audit Committee and other audiences as required 
Proven ability to partner proactively with peers, compliance partners and stakeholders 
Collect, track and analyze E&C monthly and quarterly accruals for accurate and timely submission to Finance; follow up as needed to address unresolved accruals 
Support implementation and maintenance of new strategic systems that support business goals and compliance processes (e.g. CyberGrants, HCP interactions tool, FMV tool, etc.); prepare training materials and resources; provide training and issue resolution for stakeholders; analyze data and audit systems to make recommendations for improvements 
Manage various committee meeting cadence, materials, and records. Solid understanding of governance framework in order to anticipate needs of LT members and senior leaders 
Monitor various practice area email accounts to analyze and resolve stakeholder inquiries; identify and implement protocols to proactively address recurring requests 
Support the maintenance of E&C intranet site and mobile app; analyze and recommend needed updates to continuously improve user experience 
This position will expose the associate to highly confidential personnel and corporate information, the ability to maintain the strictest confidence is necessary 
Regularly participate in Ethics Office Resolution Committee; independently prepare case summaries, including key findings and recommendations; document committee outcomes and update case information to enable accurate reporting capabilities 
Prepare and analyze Ethics Office case reports 
Ability to work with and within international laws on matters outside of the US and to recognize data privacy concerns 
Provide regular project management and data analytics support to the Privacy function of Ethics & Compliance to include projects related to US privacy laws and various GDPR laws around the world 
Develop proficiency in OneTrust privacy data platform and provide support to the Privacy function in the administration of the OneTrust privacy data platform, including analyzing and synthesizing key data points to drive improvements to global privacy compliance program 
Assist with development and roll out of policies, procedures and training on compliance program topics 
Qualifications: 
Bachelor’s degree required 
At least 5 years of relevant experience with technology, systems and/or related experience such as complex project management 
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills with ability to independently identify key issues, develop and implement creative solutions 
Experience with MS Power BI or equivalent and understanding of Artificial Intelligence (AI) capabilities required 
Prior experience supporting a legal function is a plus 
Key Attributes and Skills 
Proactive support of global team goals and objectives 
Superior communication and interpersonal and project management skills 
Ability to develop collaborative partnerships with key stakeholders 
Highly organized with superior attention to detail 
Strong analytical and writing skills and process orientation 
Advanced proficiency in office software 
Ability to understand and leverage relevant legal-specific technology tools 
Expertise in Teams, OneDrive, and Sharepoint, e.g., creating and managing folders, searching, storing, version control, sharing, etc. 
Familiarity with iCertis, sufficient to direct internal clients there and complete standard contract requests, e.g., CDAs 
Expertise in using Legal Tracker, including analyzing complex reports, reviewing and approving invoices, opening/updating matters, assigning participants, resolving vendor inquiries and invoice issues, etc. 
Advanced capabilities in Word, Excel and PowerPoint, including ability to create high-quality PowerPoint files suitable for sharing with senior leaders and Board of Directors. Use of formulas and tables in Excel 
Ability to facilitate and manage larger meetings, including logistics, scheduling, coordinating IT/AV needs, presenters, outside speakers, and directly facilitating meeting 
Self-starter with the desire and ability to take initiative 
Identify ways to simplify routine administrative and operational processes and create efficiencies 
Demonstrated ability to use sound, independent judgment in absence of leader 
Demonstrated ability to interpret and advise on relevant policies and procedures 
